This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on temporal difference learning methods, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses risk mitigation and parameter adaptation, which are related to control systems and systems engineering, respectively, so cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with estimating the variance of a quantity, which is a statistical problem, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category.
